div.div:
Generative "core system layer" graph
This graph can be used to generate iterations of useful structures like 'interface structure combinations', starting with iterations of a core layer (like a set of core functions and structures) and applying other relevant graphs like the 'uncertainty/relevance intersecting interface variable spectrum graph', to identify similarities (like spectrums) between the most relevant structures (like 'maximal differences in the system layer diagram like maximally different directions'), to generate new useful structures and identify the most relevant useful structures and their similarities.
So this means when generating new useful structures (by iterating some variable like combinations or embeddings to generate for example 'graphs, graphs of graphs, graphs of graphs of graphs', etc), patterns/similarities between the most useful structures can be identified by 'applying other graphs' or 'maximal differences' to identify relevant variation structures like 'intersections between aligned graphs' or 'relevant maximal differences'.
